http://dbpedia.org/property/desc.value: The Liberty ship ran aground on the Altair Reef . She was later refloated.
The 8-gross register ton,  fishing vessel was destroyed by fire at Koggiung, Alaska.
The ocean liner ran aground off Flores, Azores, Portugal. Two hundred passengers taken off.
The passenger ferry capsized and sank in the Aegean Sea
Vietnam War: The small 1910 coaster  was sunk by gunfire by North Vietnamese Army artillery off the Vietnamese Demilitarized Zone with the loss of her entire crew.
The coaster sank  of Cap Gris Nez following a collision with an unnamed motor vessel.
The coaster ran aground in the South China Sea  and was wrecked.
The collier foundered  off Cape Reinga with the loss of all 29 crew.
The tank ship capsized off Morgan City, Louisiana. She was on a voyage from Port Arthur, Texas to Tampa, Florida. Gulfscout was subsequently towed out to sea and sunk.
The Liberty ship ran aground at Trinidad. She was refloated, but declared a constructive total loss and scrapped.
The decommissioned  was sunk as a target by the United States Navy.
The Liberty ship ran aground at Alexandria, Egypt and broke in tow. The bow section was salvaged and subsequently used as a derrick barge.

Vietnam War: The naval trawler, a blockade runner, either was bombed and sunk by South Vietnamese Air Force aircraft or destroyed by gunfire while beached near the Ca Mau Peninsula in South Vietnam by the cutters  and  .
The 4,924-gross register ton,  barge was wrecked at Jorkins Point on Swindle Island in Milbanke Sound on the coast of the British Columbia in Canada.
The dredger collided with   in Southampton Water and sank. All eight crew rescued by Caroline M.
The 55-gross register ton,  fishing vessel was destroyed by fire in the Copper River Flats near Cordova, Alaska.
The cargo ship struck the wreck of   and sank.
The Liberty ship ran aground on the Ajax Reef . Declared a constructive total loss, she was consequently scrapped.
The Liberty ship ran aground at Hasieshan, China and broke in two.
The passenger boat sprang a leak and sank at Bridlington, Yorkshire. All 120 on board rescued by various pleasure craft. Later refloated, repaired and returned to service.
The buoy tender sank off Anchor Point, Alaska, with the loss of three lives.
The decommissioned Avenger-class escort aircraft carrier was sunk as a target by United States Navy forces.
The coaster collided with another ship and sank in the Humber Estuary.
The 17-gross register ton,  fishing vessel sank at Snettisham, Alaska.
The 163-year-old Thames barge sank at Chiswick.
The Liberty ship ran aground at Nojima Saki, Japan. Later refloated but declared a constructive total loss and scrapped.

Vietnam War: The T-333/Project 123K-class motor torpedo boats were sunk by U.S. aircraft while trying to attack the guided-missile destroyer  and the destroyer  . 19 survivors rescued and made prisoners of war.

The cargo ship ran aground at Spencer's Island, Nova Scotia, Canada. All 31 on board abandoned the ship by lifeboat and landed at Spencer's Wharf. Three local fishermen boarded the ship with the intention of salvage, but were killed when the ship exploded. Their fishing boat was also sunk.
The decommissioned  sank in the Pacific Ocean after colliding with the decommissioned high-speed transport   while both ships were under tow.
The fishing vessel was sunk by a Cuban exile-operated speedboat.
The Liberty ship ran aground in the Elbe. She was later refloated but declared a constructive total loss and scrapped.
The  was sunk as a target in the Pacific Ocean off San Francisco, California.
The 73-gross register ton,  fishing vessel was wrecked on the south-central coast of Alaska east of Ocean Cape  at .
The cargo ship ran aground on Long Sands Head Shoal,  off Harwich, Essex, United Kingdom and was wrecked. Assistance was given by the Walton on the Naze lifeboat.
The ferry ran aground in fog on a voyage between Turku, Finland and Stockholm, Sweden.
The 17-gross register ton,  fishing vessel was lost after colliding with the vessel My Laddie   off Beacon Point  in Southeast Alaska.
The 10-gross register ton motor vessel sank at Swanson Harbor  in Southeast Alaska.
The destroyer was wrecked on the coast of Galicia in Spain.
The cargo ship ran aground in the Great Belt, Denmark, while going to the assistance of Mystitchi . The teleprinter hotline between the White House and the Kremlin was cut.

The cargo ship foundered in heavy weather off Plymouth, Devon, United Kingdom. All crew 27 rescued by the tug Atlantic  or by a helicopter from 845 Naval Air Squadron based at RNAS Culdrose, Cornwall.
The Liberty ship ran aground on Sisters Shoal, Sambro Island, and was wrecked.
The 11-gross register ton,  fishing vessel was wrecked on East Amatuli Island  in the Barren Islands off the south-central coast of Alaska.
The Liberty ship collided with St. Matthew  off Irosaki, Japan. She was declared a constructive total loss and scrapped.
The 275-gross register ton,  tug was destroyed by ice at Clarks Point  in Alaska's Nushagak River.
The Liberty ship sprang a leak and was beached at Rhodes, a total loss.

The 1,450-gross register ton decommissioned destroyer escort ran aground on Sharp Park Beach, Pacifica, California after the towing cable broke. She was later scrapped onsite. .
The 10-gross register ton,  fishing vessel sank in Warner Bay  on the south coast of the Alaska Peninsula in Alaska.
The landing craft ran aground and broke up in gale off Semisopochnoi Island in the Aleutian Islands without loss of life. The seagoing buoy tender   rescued her crew.
The 74-gross register ton,  fishing vessel was lost near Narrow Cape  on Kodiak Island south of Kodiak, Alaska, after colliding with the vessel Rosemary  at .
The  refrigerator ship sank in the Bering Sea  north of Unimak Pass with the loss of about 50 lives. Soviet fishing vessels rescued about 50 survivors.
The  was driven ashore off Chu Lai, South Vietnam, by the 18-foot  surf and high winds of a typhoon.
Vietnam War: The T-25-class submarine chaser was sunk by U. S. aircraft.

The  crab-fishing vessel foundered and drifted ashore at Cape Lazaref  on Unimak Island in the Aleutian Islands, where the surf pounded her to pieces. Her four-man crew survived and was rescued from the beach, two by the tug Trojan  and two by the medium endurance cutter  .
The coaster sank in the Tagus at Lisbon, Portugal following a collision with
The cargo ship ran aground and was wrecked in the Red Sea near Jeddah, Saudi Arabia.
The 17-gross register ton,  fishing vessel was destroyed by fire at Port Lions, Alaska.
The coaster was driven ashore at Salalah, Oman during a tropical cyclone. Later repaired and returned to service.
The 13-gross register ton,  fishing vessel was destroyed by fire in Judd Harbor  on the coast of Duke Island in the Gravina Islands of the Alexander Archipelago in Southeast Alaska.
The ocean liner ran aground off Vlissingen, Netherlands. Refloated undamaged later that day.

Vietnam War: The blockade runner was run aground at Duc Pho, South Vietnam. to avoid capture. Two crewmen were killed after abandoning ship when they went back to her to check scuttling charges that failed to detonate on schedule but which detonated when they approached.
The Liberty ship sprang a leak and was abandoned off the Yucatan Peninsula, Mexico
The Liberty ship sprang a leak and foundered in the Atlantic Ocean off Cape Hatteras, North Carolina, United States.
The decommissioned sloop-of-war was sunk as a target in a nuclear weapon test in the Pacific Ocean.
The cargo ship sank in the Atlantic Ocean  northeast of Bermuda with the loss of 32 of her 38 crew.
The 20-gross register ton,  fishing vessel sank at Meyers Chuck, Alaska.
The cutter ran aground and was wrecked at Mjóvanes, Faroe Islands.
The cargo ship suffered a fire at Piraeus, Greece, and was wrecked.
The cargo ship caught fire off Arzew, Algeria, and was scuttled two days later  offshore.
The burning tanker was scuttled by the cutter  .
The 210-gross register ton,  barge sank in Chatham Strait off Takatz Island  in the Alexander Archipelago in Southeast Alaska.
A storm destroyed the barge at Sitkinak Island in the Kodiak Archipelago off Alaska.
The 12-gross register ton,  fishing vessel was destroyed by fire at Uyak , Alaska.
The coaster collided with the motor vessel   in the Kattegat and sank with the loss of six lives.
The Liberty ship ran aground on San Clemente Island, California, United States , a total loss.
The ocean liner was driven ashore in Tokyo Bay during a typhoon. Later refloated.
The tanker collided with  , and caught fire, killing 33 people on board both ships and the tugs Esso Vermont and Latin America.
A tsunami destroyed the 86-gross register ton,  barge in Cook Inlet near Anchorage, Alaska.
The Liberty ship was driven ashore near Tokyo, Japan  in a cyclone. Declared a constructive total loss, she was scrapped in situ.
The Great Lakes freighter broke up in a storm on Lake Huron with a loss of 28 of its 29 crewmen.
The roll-on/roll-off ferry capsized off the west coast of Scotland. She was salvaged and returned to service.
The ferry foundered off Cebu Island during Typhoon Irma. Of the 305 passengers and crew, at least 175 were killed.

Vietnam War: When her scuttling charges failed to detonate, the blockade runner was captured by South Vietnamese forces after running aground near the mouth of the Cổ Chiên River in the Mekong Delta in South Vietnam while trying to escape attack by the destroyer , the destroyer escort , and the dock landing ship  .
The schooner ran aground on a reef  south of Bimini, Bahamas. Fourteen of the 47 people on board were rescued by a United States Coast Guard helicopter.
The cargo ship caught fire in the Chittagong Roads, East Pakistan. She was beached but broke in two and was declared a total loss.
The cargo ship collided with    north of Ameland, Netherlands. Both ships sank, all crew rescued by Luden .
The cargo ship ran aground on Lampedusa Island in the Mediterranean Sea and sank.
The Liberty ship developed a leak and sank off the Kuria Muria Islands . All crew rescued by the   .
The fishing vessel disappeared along with both people aboard – a husband and wife – during a voyage from Seldovia to Halibut Cove, Alaska.
The passenger ferry collided with Golden State  and sank off Manila, Philippines, with the loss of 44 lives.
A storm destroyed the 337-gross register ton,  barge at East Landing  on Saint Paul Island in the Pribilof Islands.
The Liberty ship ran aground on the Alacran Reef, off the Yucatan Peninsula, Mexico. She was later refloated but declared a constructive total loss and scrapped.
Vietnam War: The cargo ship struck a mine and sank in the Saigon River in South Vietnam. She was salvaged in 1968 and scrapped.
The passenger ship ran aground at Donna Nook, Lincolnshire and capsized, killing at least thirteen people.
The decommissioned  was sunk as a target.
The Liberty ship ran aground near Okha Port, India  and broke in two, a total loss.
The 9-gross register ton,  fishing vessel was lost after she collided with an unidentified object in Chatham Strait in the Alexander Archipelago in Southeast Alaska off Point Marsden .
The 6-gross register ton,  fishing vessel sank in Cook Inlet on the south-central coast of Alaska.
The tanker was involved in a collision off Heligoland, West Germany, with the coaster  . Both ships caught fire.
The cargo ship foundered in the Irish Sea. Her crew were rescued by the Holyhead Lifeboat.
The coaster ran aground off Frinton-on-Sea, Essex, United Kingdom. Later refloated and returned to service.
The Liberty ship sprang a leak and was abandoned off the Azores . Presumed subsequently foundered.
The cargo ship ran aground in the southern Algarve. All six crew escaped alive.
The  caught fire, capsized and sank at San Juan, Puerto Rico. She was later refloated and scrapped.
The cargo ship collided with the Bull lightvessel  and sank at the mouth of the Humber.
The train ferry sank in the North Sea with the loss of two of the 147 people on board.
The cargo liner ran aground in Table Bay on the coast of South Africa and broke in two. All 76 people on board were rescued by South African Air Force helicopters.
The Liberty ship was driven ashore and wrecked in a typhoon at Madras, India.
A tsunami destroyed the barge at Sitkinak Island in the Kodiak Archipelago off Alaska.
The Liberty ship suffered a fractured hull and was abandoned in the Pacific Ocean . Presumed subsequently foundered.

The 24-gross register ton,  fishing vessel sank off a location identified in the wreck report as "Seal Cape Light" on the coast of Alaska. The report does not specify to which of several locations known as Seal Cape in Alaska it refers.

The tanker ran aground in New York Bay,  east of Sandy Hook, New Jersey, United States. Thirty-nine crew taken off by the pilot boat New Jersey . Thirteen crew and a pilot taken off the next day by  . The ship was later refloated, repaired and returned to service.

During a voyage from Ketchikan in Southeast Alaska to Kodiak on Kodiak Island with five men, one woman, and a cargo of lumber on board, the 194-gross register ton,  fishing vessel disappeared without trace in a storm in the Gulf of Alaska.
The 8-gross register ton,  fishing vessel was wrecked in southwest Alaska on the Kvichak River between King Salmon Creek and Copenhagen Creek.
The coaster sank between the Isles of Scilly and Penzance, Cornwall after her cargo shifted. All seven crew rescued by  .
The Channel tanker sank south of Cyprus.
The decommissioned  was sunk as a target in the Pacific Ocean off San Clemente Island, California, by a combination of naval gunfire and aircraft attacks.
The decommissioned  was sunk as a target in the Pacific Ocean off San Nicolas Island in Californiaʼs Channel Islands by surface gunfire and by aircraft from the attack aircraft carrier  .
The coaster foundered north west of Hook of Holland, Netherlands. All four crew survived.
The cargo ship was involved in a collision in the Strait of Dover, and was beached at Sandown, Kent.
The decommissioned Fletcher-class destroyer was sunk as a target in the Pacific Ocean off the coast of California.
The motor vessel sank off Deer Island  in Nelson Lagoon, Alaska.

While under tow from the Pacific Northwest to Alaska, where she was to be employed as a floating cannery, the retired 526-gross register ton,  ferry sank approximately  northwest of Tonki Cape Light  on the south-central coast of Alaska.
The ocean liner caught fire at New York. The fire developed in the engine room and gutted five decks.
The Liberty ship foundered in the Atlantic Ocean .
The Liberty ship collided with Funabashi  off Singapore . She capsized and sank.
The 12-gross register ton,  fishing vessel was destroyed by a storm in the Gulf of Alaska off Aiaktalik Island  in the Kodiak Archipelago.

The former range instrumentation ship was intentionally grounded on a sand bar in the Chesapeake Bay  east of Point Lookout, Maryland, between Point Lookout and Smith Island, Maryland, at  for use as an aerial bombing target.
The tanker exploded whilst her cargo of naptha was being unloaded in New York Harbor, killing four people.
The coaster caught fire, then capsized and sank off Jeddah, Saudi Arabia.
The cargo ship ran aground in the Great Belt, Denmark.
The Liberty ship was driven ashore in a typhoon at Kaohsiung, Taiwan. She was declared a constructive total loss and scrapped.
The cargo ship, a converted , was scuttled off Cape Spencer, Nova Scotia.
Vietnam War: The LCS-class landing ship was sunk by the North Vietnamese 126th Special Naval Commandos with limpet mines.
The 22-gross register ton,  fishing vessel sank off Craig, Alaska.
The Liberty ship sprang a leak and was abandoned in the Atlantic Ocean  east of Cape Race, Canada. Presumed subsequently sank.
The Liberty ship was driven ashore at Mapingil, Philippines.
The 9-gross register ton,  fishing vessel was wrecked in Aniakchak Bay  on the Gulf of Alaska coast of the Alaska Peninsula.
The Liberty ship ran aground off Pulo Sambu, Indonesia. She was later refloated and towed to Singapore where she was declared a constructive total loss.
